The paper deals with Boolean functions and their properties, which are central to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The concept of noisy influence is related to information theory (cs.IT) and the study of random graphs (cs.SI). Finally, the application of the regularity lemma to the Majority is Stablest Theorem involves combinatorics and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
